An epithelium that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].
An epithelium that is part of a digestive system [Automatically generated definition].
An epithelium that is part of a salivary gland [Automatically generated definition].

A gland that is part of a eye. The eye is a compound unit which depending on the species may consist of an eyeballs plus associated ducts and integumentary structures. Eye glands therefore include the various types of lacrimal gland, the various types of apocrine and sebaceous glands associated with the eyelid.

label.value: somatic layer of lateral plate mesoderm

definition.value: Layer of lateral plate mesoderm that forms the future body wall - underlies the ectoderm[WP].

label.value: splanchnic layer of lateral plate mesoderm

definition.value: Layer of lateral plate mesoderm that forms the circulatory system and future gut wall - overlies endoderm[WP].

a structure created during embryogenesis when the lateral mesoderm splits into two layers - the outer (or somatic) layer becomes applied to the inner surface of the ectoderm, and with it forms the somatopleure.[WP].
A portion of the gut that is derived from ectoderm.
the region of the digestive tract extending from the beginning of the intestines to the anus[GO - gut definition].
An epithelium surrounding a gonad.
An epithelium surrounding a testis.
An epithelium surrounding an ovary.
A proximal-distal subdivision of the digestive tract.
Organ component which is a part of a wall of an organ.
A mucosa that is part of an ascending colon [Automatically generated definition].
A mucosa that is part of a fallopian tube [Automatically generated definition].
An external genitalia that is part of a female reproductive system [Automatically generated definition].
The median dorsal longitudinal groove formed in the embryo by the neural plate after the appearance of the neural folds.
One of the two elevated edges of the neural groove[GO,MP].
An ectodermal placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that is the primordium of many structures derived from the ectoderm[GO]
Muscle structures are contractile cells, tissues or organs that are found in multicellular organisms[GO].
An anatomical structure that is part of the reproductive system.
An epithelial sheet bent on a linear axis.
A structure consisting of multiple cell components but which is not itself a cell and does not have (complete) cells as a part.
An organ that part of the adbominal segment of the organism. This region can be further subdivided into the abdominal cavity and the pelvic region.
An organ that part of the trunk region. The trunk region can be further subdividied into thoracic (including chest and thoracic cavity) and abdominal (including abdomen and pelbis) regions.
An organ that is in the thoracic cavity. Examples: lung, heart.
An organ that is part of the pelvic region. Examples: reproductive organs (in some organisms), urinary bladder.
An organ that part of the thoracic segment region. This region can be further subdividied chest and thoracic cavity regions.
A vein that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].
A gland that is part of a stomodeum.

Portion of primordial embryonic connective tissue of the developing head, consisting of mesenchymal cells supported in interlaminar jelly, that derive mostly from the mesoderm and contribute to head connective tissue, bone and musculature in conjunction with cranial neural crest cells.
Mesenchyme that is part of a trunk.
A vasculature that is part of a brain [Automatically generated definition].
A portion of tissue that is part of an embryo.
Portion of tissue that is contiguous with the embryo and is comprised of portions of tissue or cells that will not contribute to the embryo.
A sex gland that is part of a female reproductive system.
A sex gland that is part of a male reproductive system.
Portion of tissue that gives rise to the immature gonad.
the amnion and chorion which surround and protect a developing fetus.
Intrinsic membrane that arises from embryonic germ layers and grow to surround the developing embryo.
An epithelium that is part of a caecum.
An epithelium that is part of a ear vesicle.
A sensory system that is capable of olfacttion (the sensory perception of smell).

a round nodule, small eminence, or warty outgrowth found on bones, skin, or within the lungs in tuberculosis. They are also found on the leading edge of Humpback Whale's flippers, improving fluid flow over the flipper's surface[WP].
